SIMPLE: optical properties with optimal basis functions

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Standard compilation: run "make gwl"

 
Directory Structure: 
simple                      : source files for construction of the optimal basis (simple.x executable)
simple_ip                   : source files for IP calculation of optical properties (simple_ip.x executable)
simple_bse                  : source files for BSE calculation of optical properties (simple_bse.x executable)

util                        : gen_kgrid.py       --> python script that generates an uniform k-grid in the Brillouin zone with the possibility to include the periodic images of the Gamma point
                              abcoeff_to_eps.f90 --> calculate dielectric function from the coefficients of the Haydock's recursive scheme

examples/example04  : example for IP optical properties (bulk silver)
examples/example05  : example for BSE optical properties (bulk silicon)
